    id: 'lesson-18', title: 'std::string', category: 'arrays', order_index: 18,
    content: '## The std::string Class\n\nModern, safe, convenient string type. Manages memory automatically.\n\n## Creating Strings\n```cpp\n#include <string>\nstring s1;                // Empty\nstring s2 = "Hello";\nstring s3(5, \'A\');         // "AAAAA"\nstring s4 = s2 + " World"; // Concatenation\n```\n\n## Common Operations\n\n### Size and Access\n```cpp\nstring s = "Hello";\ns.length();    // 5\ns.size();      // 5\ns[0];          // \'H\' (no bounds check)\ns.at(0);       // \'H\' (throws if invalid)\ns.front();     // \'H\'\ns.back();      // \'o\'\ns.c_str();     // const char*\n```\n\n### Modification\n```cpp\ns += " World";        // Append\ns.append("!");        // "Hello World!"\ns.insert(5, " cruel"); // "Hello cruel World!"\ns.erase(5, 6);        // "Hello World!"\ns.replace(6, 5, "Earth"); // "Hello Earth!"\ns.clear();            // ""\n```\n\n### Searching\n```cpp\ns.find("World");        // 6 (position)\ns.rfind(\'o\');           // 7 (last occurrence)\ns.find_first_of("aeiou"); // 1 (\'e\')\n\nif (s.find("xyz") == string::npos) {\n    // Not found!\n}\n```\n\n### Conversion\n```cpp\nint i = stoi("42");\ndouble d = stod("3.14");\nstring s = to_string(42);  // "42"\n```\n\n## Performance Tips\n1. Pass by const string& to avoid copying\n2. Use reserve() if you know final size\n3. s += c is faster than s = s + c',
